Description: A single text column that provides a detailed description of the study protocol.
Example: CD4-specific CAR is a chimeric antigen receptor immunotherapy treatment designed to treat lymphoma/leukemia expressing CD4 antigen. CD4+ T cell lymphomas are a subset of leukemias and lymphomas that are positive for the surface protein CD4. The purpose of this study is to evaluate the efficacy and safety of CD4 CAR T cells.
notes: Some terminated trials embed their stop reasons in the detailed description. This field may contain post-trial information and requires manual screening before inclusion in the LLM input.

Description: A single text column that provides a brief description of the study.
Example: This is a phase I, interventional, single arm, open label, treatment study to evaluate the safety and tolerability of CD4 CAR T cells in patients with relapsed and/or refractory T cell lymphoma.

notes: Detailed masking information is available for four roles (subject, caregiver, investigator, outcomes assessor). These may be useful features, and we may consider including them in the LLM input.
